ecuring economic growth, encouraging innovation, reducing taxes, making government efficient and reforming entitlement programs. during his tenure as chairman of subcommittee on human resources, congressman herger played a leading role in the reauthorization and expansion of the landmark 1996 welfare reform law. he got his start in elected office as a member of the east nicolaus school board, serving there from 1976 to 1980. he was elected to the california state assembly in 1980, serving there until his election to the united states house of representatives by the people of california's second congressional district.</p></span>



